						<additions>
							<p>A note on f. 4r describes the author, <persName
									xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7392">Muḥammad Rashīd
									al-Dīn Dihlavī</persName> in adulatory terms and as deceased,
								indicating that the writer, perhaps a former owner, was a firm
								Sunni, writing after 1243/1827-8, the year of Rashīd al-Dīn's death. </p>
							<p>Some marginal notes. </p>
							<p>Contents note listing 3 works on f. i recto. </p>
						</additions>
